<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,1135,1274]" box="[189,303,1135,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1135,1161]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1135,1161]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,1135,1274]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
This species is distributed in the north and east of Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Askew R. R." box="[882,1035,1177,1203]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="263 - 264" refId="ref10942" refString="Askew R. R. 1970. Encyrtidae (Hym., Chalcidoidea) new to Britain. Entomologist 103: 263 - 264." type="journal article" year="1970">Askew 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kalina, V." box="[1047,1195,1177,1203]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="97 - 127" refId="ref11799" refString="Kalina, V. 1989. Checklist of Czechoslovak Insects III (Hymenoptera). Chalcidoidea. Acta Faunistica Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 19: 97 - 127." type="journal article" year="1989">Kalina 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Trjapitzin V. A." box="[1207,1390,1177,1203]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 489" refId="ref12477" refString="Trjapitzin V. A. 1989. Parasitic Hymenoptera of the Fam. Encyrtidae of Palaearctics. Opredeliteli po Faune SSSR 158: 1 - 489." type="journal article" year="1989">Trjapitzin 1989</bibRefCitation>
) and represents a new record from 
<collectingCountry box="[583,634,1213,1239]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The biology of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffer" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[823,950,1213,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Echthroplexiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[823,950,1213,1239]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">E. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still unknown, but the species could be associated with a pseudococcid species on 
<taxonomicName box="[727,859,1248,1274]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[727,859,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1305,1579]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Some of the more important diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffer" baseAuthorityYear="1954" box="[835,965,1306,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Echthroplexiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[835,965,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">E. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: body length of female 
<quantity box="[1306,1398,1305,1332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
(range 
<quantity box="[271,415,1341,1367]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.6 mm</quantity>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Trjapitzin V. A." box="[427,613,1341,1368]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="851 - 860" refId="ref12504" refString="Trjapitzin V. A. 2006. A review of the encyrtid genus Echthroplexiella Mercet, 1921 (Hymenoptera, Encyrtidae) of the World with description of a new species from Mexico. Entomological Review 86: 851 - 860. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873806070086" type="journal article" year="2006">Trjapitzin 2006</bibRefCitation>
); body brownish-yellow to light brown with dark brown metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[197,290,1376,1402]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1039,1065]" captionTargetBox="[319,1300,265,993]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[313,1300,265,993]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Echthroplexiella obscura (Hoffer, 1954). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011132/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); scape much (4×) longer than wide, funicular segments wider than long, claval segments fused, obliquely truncate, shorter than the funiculus (
<figureCitation box="[757,855,1411,1437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1039,1065]" captionTargetBox="[319,1300,265,993]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[313,1300,265,993]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Echthroplexiella obscura (Hoffer, 1954). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011132/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); notauli complete (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1198,1411,1437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1039,1065]" captionTargetBox="[319,1300,265,993]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[313,1300,265,993]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Echthroplexiella obscura (Hoffer, 1954). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011132/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); brachypterous, forewing with 2 wide transverse dark bands, middle large band occupying their whole width, distal band broad, faintly fading away to the margin of the wing, hyaline band between the two bands very narrow; marginal vein 2× as long as broad, postmarginal vein as long as broad, stigma vein a little longer than broad; protruding part of ovipositor sheath longer than 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,860,1552,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">1⁄5</emphasis>
of the length of metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1284,1552,1578]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1039,1065]" captionTargetBox="[319,1300,265,993]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[313,1300,265,993]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Echthroplexiella obscura (Hoffer, 1954). A. Female in lateral view. B. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. C. Antenna of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011132" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011132/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
